<hl>
<seg id=1> McLaren And Zhou Jiahua Hold Talks </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Toronto, April 22: Roy McLaren, Canada's minister of international trade, received a visit here today from Zhou Jiahua, vice-premier of China's State Council. He said that he had just returned from a visit to China, and that the speedy development of China's economy had left a deep impression upon him. </seg>
<seg id=3> He firmly believes that Canada and China can become good cooperation partners. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> McLaren reaffirmed his support both of the reinstatement of China's contracting party status in the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade, and of China's bid to become a member of the World Trade Organization. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Zhou Jiahua said that in the few days that he has been in Canada he has felt personally the way that the Canadian government and people at various levels have shown a strong desire to strengthen cooperation with China. He also feels that the conditions for speeding up development of the relationship between the two countries are already there, and that the moment is advantageous. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> McLaren and Zhou Jiahua also investigated the prospects of Canada and China's cooperation in the realms of trade and technology. </seg>
<seg id=7> Both sides believe that even though the trade relationship will see big growth over the next few years, the two countries' practical needs and current potential dictate that it's still far from enough. </seg>
<seg id=8> In terms of energy resources, transportation, hydro-electricity, communications and other areas of infrastructure, the two countries have great potential to expand their cooperation. </seg>
<seg id=9> Both sides exchanged views and reached wide agreement on specific issues. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> McLaren held a dinner to entertain Zhou Jiahua and his party after the talks were over. </seg>
</p>
